OL,3,GEast Midlands
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA dry day with long sunny
OL,6,Fspells and increasingly strong
OL,7,Feasterly winds, with a chance of gales
OL,8,Fover the Peak District. Warm inland
OL,9,Fbut cooler along coasts.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FA dry evening with some late
OL,12,Fsunny spells, though remaining windy.
OL,13,FA clear night will follow, becoming
OL,14,Fchilly. Winds abating a little, though
OL,15,Fa brisk breeze will remain.
OL,16,
OL,17,CThursday:FAnother day of long sunny
OL,18,Fspells, though windy once again, these
OL,19,Fstrongest near coasts. Warm, though
OL,20,Ffeeling cooler in exposed areas and
OL,21,Falong eastern coasts.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
